statement.summary: MariaDB 10.5 has security support until June 2025
statement.text: Support period for MariaDB 10.5 differs from the main distribution end-of-life date.

statement.summary: NGINX has security support until March 2028
statement.text: AL2023 will keep ingesting new upstream NGINX releases.

statement.summary: PHP 8.1 has security support until November 2025
statement.text: Support period for PHP 8.1 differs from the main distribution end-of-life date.

statement.summary: PostgreSQL 15 has security support until November 2027
statement.text: Support period for PostgreSQL 15 differs from the main distribution end-of-life date.

statement.summary: Python 3.9 (System Python) has security support until March 2028
statement.text: AL2023 has Python 3.9 as the System Python. Amazon will continue to security patch this version of Python until the end-of-life of AL2023, which is beyond when upstream Python supports this version until.

statement.summary: Redis 6 has security support until August 2025
statement.text: The support period for Redis 6 is specific to Redis 6.2 end-of-life period. AL2023 will keep ingesting minor versions of Redis 6 as they become available.

statement.summary: Ruby 3.2 has security support until March 2026
statement.text: Support period for Ruby 3.2 differs from the main distribution end-of-life date.

statement.summary: PCRE has security support until June 2024
statement.text: pcre version 1 is deprecated, replaced by pcre2. This support period is to allow migration time for remaining pcre version 1 users.

statement.summary: Dotnet6.0 has security support until November 2024
statement.text: Support period for Dotnet6.0 differs from the main distribution end-of-life date.
This is the support statement for AL2023. The end-of-life of Amazon Linux 2023 is March 2028. From this point, the Amazon Linux 2023 packages will no longer receive any updates from AWS.
